{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.7",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 7 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:1",
      "text": "My son, keep my words, and lay up my precepts with thee. Son,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:2",
      "text": "Keep my commandments, and thou shalt live: and my law as the apple of thy eye:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:3",
      "text": "Bind it upon thy fingers, write it upon the tables of thy heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:4",
      "text": "Say to wisdom: Thou art my sister: and call prudence thy friend,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:5",
      "text": "That she may keep thee from the woman that is not thine, and from the stranger who sweeteneth her words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:6",
      "text": "For I looked out of the window of my house through the lattice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:7",
      "text": "And I see little ones, I behold a foolish young man,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:8",
      "text": "Who passeth through the street by the corner, and goeth nigh the way of her house,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:9",
      "text": "In the dark when it grows late, in the darkness and obscurity of the night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:10",
      "text": "And behold a woman meeteth him in harlot's attire, prepared to deceive souls: talkative and wandering,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:11",
      "text": "Not bearing to be quiet, not able to abide still at home,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:12",
      "text": "Now abroad, now in the streets, now lying in wait near the corners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:13",
      "text": "And catching the young man, she kisseth him, and with an impudent face, flattereth, saying:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:14",
      "text": "I vowed victims for prosperity, this day I have paid my vows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:15",
      "text": "Therefore I am come out to meet thee, desirous to see thee, and I have found thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:16",
      "text": "I have woven my bed with cords, I have covered it with painted tapestry, brought from Egypt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:17",
      "text": "I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:18",
      "text": "Come, let us be inebriated with the breasts, and let us enjoy the desired embraces, till the day appear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:19",
      "text": "For my husband is not at home, he is gone a very long journey.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:20",
      "text": "He took with him a bag of money: he will return home the day of the full moon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:21",
      "text": "She entangled him with many words, and drew him away with the flattery of her lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:22",
      "text": "Immediately he followeth her as an ox led to be a victim, and as a lamb playing the wanton, and not knowing that he is drawn like a fool to bonds,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:23",
      "text": "Till the arrow pierce his liver: as if a bird should make haste to the snare, and knoweth not that his life is in danger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:24",
      "text": "Now, therefore, my son, hear me, and attend to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:25",
      "text": "Let not thy mind be drawn away in her ways: neither be thou deceived with her paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:26",
      "text": "For she hath cast down many wounded, and the strongest have been slain by her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.7.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:27",
      "text": "Her house is the way to hell, reaching even to the inner chambers of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
